<h2><a name="Tour highlights"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Tour highlights</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Spend 11 days exploring Italy by rail</li>
<li>Stay in comfortable three or four-star hotels in Rome, <a data-udi="umb://document/8b79e45930f145f6b156a9152415fa9b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8b79e45930f145f6b156a9152415fa9b}" title="Florence">Florence</a>, La Spezia, Milan and Venice</li>
<li>Use the fantastic high speed train network to get around</li>
<li>Experience Imperial Rome on an excursion to see the Colosseum &amp; Roman Forum</li>
<li>Visit Naples and see how the Romans once lived in Pompeii</li>
<li>Explore Tuscany’s Siena, San Gimignano &amp; the Chianti wine region, for a wine tasting experience</li>
<li>Use your Cinque Terre Card to explore the UNESCO villages</li>
<li>Head for Lake Como to explore the historic city of Como, before cruising across to Bellagio</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/amalfi-coast-walking#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Itinerary"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Itinerary</span></h2>
<p><strong>Day 1: UK to Rome</strong></p>
<p>Fly into Rome and transfer to your hotel in the city.</p>
<p>Meals included: none</p>
<p><strong>Day 2: Rome</strong></p>
<p>Spend your fist day in Italy’s buzzing history filled capital, Rome. Discover the imperial city on a group tour of the Colosseum and Roman Forum. Choose what you get up to for the rest of the day - stroll through ivory covered piazzas, climb the Spanish steps up to Trinita dei Monti, toss a coin in the Trevi Fountain, visit the pope in the Vatican City, eat, drink and explore.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 3: Naples</strong></p>
<p>Take a day trip to Naples – the city sprawls around the bay at the foot of Mount Vesuvius. Start with a walking tour, soaking up the sights, sounds and noises of the city. Walking along the Spaccanapoli, the narrow street that divides the historic centre, you’ll get a feel for the place. Get an introduction to the historical sights like the Piazza del Plebiscito with its neoclassical Royal Palace and the Duomo. While you’re here in the birth place of Pizza - you’ve got to try a slice. In the afternoon you’ll have a guided visit of Pompeii and learn all about the Roman civilisation that inhabited the once thriving city.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast, Light Lunch</p>
<p><strong>Day 4: Rome to Florence</strong></p>
<p>This morning, board the high speed train to Florence. Spend the afternoon exploring the Renaissance city. If art’s your thing, you’ll be in your element. The entire city’s like an open air gallery, with beautiful art and architecture at every turn. Climb up to the lookout point at Piazzale Michelangelo for views across the city and surrounding countryside – spot the terracotta domed roof of the Cathedral of Santa Maria del Fiore towering above it all.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 5: Siena, San Gimignano and Chianti</strong></p>
<p>Get a feel for <a data-udi="umb://document/58d85ec0faa548b2ab580143fdc9b722" href="/{localLink:umb://document/58d85ec0faa548b2ab580143fdc9b722}" title="Tuscany &amp; Umbria">Tuscany</a> on a full day tour of the region. You’ll travel by coach to the Chianti area to visit Monteriggioni - the fortified citadel, that started out as a castle. Have a look around and enjoy the views across the vineyard filled Chianti landscape. On to Siena where the historic centre’s a UNESCO World Heritage Site – you’ll understand why as you explore Piazza del Campo, Piazza Duomo, Palazzo Pubblico and the famous Torre del Mangia. Next stop on the tour is the walled town of San Gimignano, known for its Etruscan towers. It would be hard to come here to the wine region without the chance to try it for yourself, so we’ve included a wine tasting experience at a <a data-udi="umb://document/8502468fe6eb499faab16739425f51ec" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8502468fe6eb499faab16739425f51ec}" title="Siena &amp; Chianti">Chianti</a> vineyard.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 6: Florence to La Spezia</strong></p>
<p>Take the train from Florence to the Ligurian coast. You’ll have the afternoon free to explore the pastel-coloured fishing village of La Spezia. Check out the local trattorias in the old town for an authentic Ligurian lunch. You could even venture over to Portovenere or start exploring the Cinque Terre Villages – all reachable by train.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 7: Cinque Terre </strong></p>
<p>Make the most of your <a data-udi="umb://document/c0a1a2eb5f21493d858ec9013916a8fb" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c0a1a2eb5f21493d858ec9013916a8fb}" title="Liguria">Cinque Terre</a> &amp; Train Card, by spending the day exploring Monterosso, Vernazza, Corniglia, Manarola and Riomaggiore. You can use it to hop between the villages and gives you access to the beautiful walking trails that hug the coast.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 8: La Spezia to Milan</strong></p>
<p>On the next part of your rail journey you'll go from La Spezia to <a data-udi="umb://document/2575554a5b50446eb00d5bf533f317cd" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2575554a5b50446eb00d5bf533f317cd}" title="Milan">Milan</a>. To fit in with the Milanese style, wear your chicest outfit to explore the fashion capital and its shops, art galleries and restaurants. In Milan aperitivo is a ritual, come 6pm the bars and cafes throng with a lively atmosphere. It feels as if the whole cities joining in – so you should too. Find a table, order a spritz and the rest is history.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 9: Lake Como</strong></p>
<p>Italy’s lake district’s not far from Milan, so we’ve included a full day excursion to the beautiful <a data-udi="umb://document/7d421e04a79044babf8cafda30e31d4a" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7d421e04a79044babf8cafda30e31d4a}" title="Lake Como">Lake Como</a>, at the foothills of the Alps. Start your tour in Como’s historic centre, where you’ll have free time to wander, visit the churches, or even shop. Next head across to <a data-udi="umb://document/d3611d3782e0494ead59e534458bcdd6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d3611d3782e0494ead59e534458bcdd6}" title="Bellagio">Bellagio</a>, taking the scenic route by ferry. The views are amazing – elegant villas line the lake shores and you might even spot Villa d'Este at Cernobbio, a luxurious hotel set in tropical gardens. Bellagio’s one of the most famous towns on the lake. Weave your way through the cobbled streets up from the lake and stop for a coffee or gelato at one of the lively cafes. Spend some time looking around town before taking another boat on to Cadenabbia. After, you’ll be taken by coach back to Milan.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 10: Milan to Venice</strong></p>
<p>This morning, take the high speed train from Milan to <a data-udi="umb://document/201893063f65496384a9bd17846543a7" href="/{localLink:umb://document/201893063f65496384a9bd17846543a7}" title="Venice">Venice</a> – watch out the window as you pass through beautiful landscapes on your way to Italy’s east coast. Soak up the hustle and bustle of St Mark’s Square and the Grand Canal or escape to the more tranquil side streets and small canals that crisscross the city.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 11: Venice to UK</strong></p>
<p>Make your way to Venice airport for your flight home.</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/amalfi-coast-walking#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Your holiday includes"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Your holiday includes</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>10 nights’ bed &amp; breakfast accommodation</li>
<li>Staying in 3-star hotels (includes one 4-star hotel) or exclusively 4-star hotels (available on request)</li>
<li>Airport transfers</li>
<li>Second class high speed train tickets with seat reservations &amp; one piece of luggage per person (First class upgrades available for a supplement, on request)</li>
<li>Regional train from Florence to La Spezia</li>
<li>48-hour Cinque Terre Card for train travel around the villages and access to the paths of the National Park (day 6 &amp; 7)</li>
<li>Skip the line Imperial Rome excursion: Colosseum &amp; Roman Forum (approx. 3 hours, day 2)</li>
<li>Naples and Pompeii excursion, with light lunch (full day by coach, day 3)</li>
<li>Siena, San Gimignano &amp; Chianti excursion, with light lunch &amp; wine tasting (full day by coach, day 5)</li>
<li>Lake Como: Como &amp; Bellagio excursion (full day, day 9)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Your holiday excludes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Transfers from/to the train stations (all hotels are within walking distance)</li>
<li>Any extras, drinks and personal expenses</li>
<li>Hotel city tax</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Please note that the itinerary of the tour and the days of excursions may be modified for technical reasons</em></p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a style="text-align: right;" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-italy/amalfi-coast-walking#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Hotels"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Hotels</span></h2>
<p><strong>★★★</strong><strong> Hotel San Marco, Rome (3 nights)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★</strong><strong> Hotel Alinari, Florence (2 nights)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★★</strong><strong> Hotel The Poet, La Spezia or Hotel Palme, Monterosso (for a supplement, on request) (2 nights) </strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★</strong><strong> Hotel Ibis Milano Centro, Milan (2 nights)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★</strong><strong> Hotel Carlton Capri, Venice (1 night)</strong></p>
<p><strong>OR </strong></p>
<p><em>to upgrade to the following (or similar) exclusively four-star hotel’s please call to book:</em></p>
<p><strong>★★★★ </strong><strong>Hotel Mediterraneo, Rome (3 nights)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★★ </strong><strong>Hotel Executive, Florence (2 nights)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★★ </strong><strong>Hotel The Poet, La Spezia (2 nights)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★★ </strong><strong>Hotel Adi Doria, Milan (2 nights)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★★ </strong><strong>Hotel Amadeus, Venice (1 night)</strong></p>
<p><em>Please note that all of the hotels are subject to availability at the time of booking. If they are not available, they’ll be changed to hotels of a similar standard and location.</em></p>
<h2><a name="Departure dates"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Departure dates<a></a></span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Daily departures from May to October</li>
<li>Wednesday and Thursday departures are available on request, please call to book</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
